<body>
    <h1>Recall from Leave of Absence</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">
<div class=3D"columnLayout fixed-width" data-layout=3D"fixed-width">
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">
<div class=3D"innerCell">
<p>Table-23</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"center" data-local-id=3D"00=
54cd0e-680f-4292-b2f4-b0717d9216f5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 257.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1542.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Type</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Leave Of Absence (LOA)&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The LOA use case describes the recall from Leave Of Absence process for =
user identities in SailPoint IIQ. SailPoint will automatically Enable acces=
s privileges in SailPoint and the associated downstream systems.&nbsp;</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>List of Attributes&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The following set of attributes represent the tentative set of users=E2=
=80=99 attributes which will be used in the process flow. The final set of =
source and target attributes will be finalized in the solution design docum=
ent.</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>First Name&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Last Name&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Person Number&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Assignment Status&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>System Worker Type&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Action Name&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Start Date&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Hire Date&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Effective Date&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Department&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Position&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Location&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Termination date&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Ministry</p></li>
<li>
<p>Effective Start Date</p></li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Refer Appendix =E2=80=9C<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://drive=
.google.com/drive/folders/17u4oN4VdyLijziIcn8PMSlUxT5HS_LW0" rel=3D"nofollo=
w"><u>Source and Target Attribute Mapping</u></a>=E2=80=9D for complete lis=
t of attribute mapping.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pre-Conditions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User is already present in SailPoint IdentityIQ with existing accounts a=
nd access details.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Trigger</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When following conditions are true:</p>
<p>Data present in HCM feed will be used to identify the associate=E2=80=99=
s recall from LOA condition.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The final list of trigger condition will be confirmed by the HR te=
am.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Basic Flow</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>User account will be enabled in SailPoint IdentityIQ.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IdentityIQ will provision the birthright access to the AD acco=
unt&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Oracle ERP Cloud Account of the user&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IdentityIQ will also enable other downstream application accou=
nts of the</p></li>
<li>
<p>user except Active Directory and GSuite.</p></li>
</ol>
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>List of downstream applications</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Active Directory, Azure, GSuite, ServiceNow, Oracle ERP Cloud, Oracle EP=
M Cloud, OCI.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Acceptance criteria</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The SailPoint IdentityIQ Account will be Enabled</p></li>
<li>
<p>Birthright Access provisioning will be done for AD Account and ERP Cloud=
 Account of the user.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The User=E2=80=99s accounts for other downstream applications are enable=
d.</p></li>
</ol></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Error handling</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A ServiceNow ticket will be created and assigned to the Ascension Health=
 Alliance SailPoint IIQ support team.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d9e2f3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Persona / Actors</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Automated Process</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Dependency:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"976" data-layout=3D"center" data-local-id=3D"b57=
c2f20-8e6a-4b37-9abd-40d94836cb08" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 84.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 154.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 736.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d4deec" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>S. no</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d4deec" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dependency</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d4deec" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Point of contact for answers</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>List of attributes</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Oracle HCM Cloud application team to send the final set of attributes ma=
pping.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Trigger</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Oracle HCM Cloud application team to finalize the attributes and its val=
ues required for trigger.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Basic Flow</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Oracle HCM Cloud application team to finalize the attributes and its val=
ues required in the Basic Flow.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Recall from Leave of Absence Flow Diagram</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
